      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(tart): desktop/VNC support via guest Screen Sharing",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdd first-class Tart macOS desktop support:\n\n- `crabbox warmup --provider tart --desktop` enables native macOS Screen Sharing and verifies its RFB listener before reporting ready.\n- `crabbox webvnc --provider tart --id <lease>` opens a browser viewer through a host-side noVNC/WebSocket bridge and SSH tunnel; the guest needs no noVNC tooling.\n- `crabbox screenshot --provider tart --id <lease>` captures the macOS desktop noninteractively with the configured guest account credentials.\n- Explicit `--arch arm64` is accepted for Tart, while explicit `--arch amd64` is rejected.\n- Kept Tart VMs now survive the launching Crabbox process and terminal session exiting.\n\n## Design\n\n### Guest\n\n- Tart still runs the VM headless with `tart run <name> --no-graphics`.\n- Desktop leases enable `com.apple.screensharing` through `tart exec`.\n- Acquisition waits for `127.0.0.1:5900` inside the guest and fails if Screen Sharing does not become ready.\n- Screen Sharing uses the guest account's Apple/ARD credentials. Crabbox does not provision a separate VNC password.\n\n### Browser bridge\n\n- SSH forwards a host loopback port to guest `127.0.0.1:5900`.\n- Crabbox serves only `/credentials` and `/websockify` on literal `127.0.0.1`.\n- The viewer is a self-contained mode-0600 temporary HTML file containing the vendored noVNC module and a per-session bearer.\n- The browser URL is a local `file://` path. Passwords and bearer values do not appear in the URL, process arguments, cookies, or DNS.\n- `/credentials` requires `POST`, `Origin: null`, and a constant-time token match. It returns `Cache-Control: no-store`.\n- `/websockify` requires the matching secret WebSocket subprotocol before upgrade.\n- The reusable guest password is fetched into browser memory and is not written into the handoff file.\n\n### Process lifetime\n\nKept Tart VMs run in a new process session with regular-file/null stdio, so terminal or tmux teardown does not stop the VM. Immediate `tart run` failures still preserve up to 64 KiB of startup stderr for diagnostics.\n\n## Security boundary\n\nmacOS Screen Sharing binds guest interfaces and is reachable from the Tart host-local network, protected by guest account authentication. The browser bridge and SSH tunnel bind only to host loopback. This intentional boundary and remote-controller forwarding procedure are documented in `docs/providers/tart.md`.\n\n## Live proof\n\nVerified June 10, 2026 on Apple Silicon, macOS 26.5, Tart 2.32.1, Go 1.26.4, exact PR head `7b830c1baf51e9d030fcc7d8567b8cbf9b42ac57`.\n\n```text\n$ crabbox warmup --provider tart --target macos --arch arm64 --desktop --slug pr246-final --keep=true\nConnection to 127.0.0.1 port 5900 [tcp/rfb] succeeded!\nprovisioned lease=cbx_ae052863e6c1 instance=crabbox-pr246-final-c1d889da state=ready\nready ssh=admin@192.168.65.2:22 network=public workroot=/Users/admin/crabbox\nwarmup complete total=15.721s\n```\n\nAfter Crabbox and its tmux session exited:\n\n```text\ntart list: crabbox-pr246-final-c1d889da Running=true State=running\nprocess: PPID=1, tart run crabbox-pr246-final-c1d889da --no-graphics\n```\n\nBrowser path:\n\n```text\n$ crabbox webvnc --provider tart --id cbx_ae052863e6c1 --local-port 15901\nbridge: serving noVNC locally; SSH tunnel -> guest 127.0.0.1:5900\nwebvnc: file:///.../crabbox-webvnc-....html\n\nhandoff mode: -rw-------\nChrome -> 127.0.0.1:15901: ESTABLISHED\ncredentials GET: 405\ncredentials POST with bad token: 403\ncredentials POST with valid token and Origin null: 200\nsecret in process arguments: no\n```\n\nReal Chrome rendered the guest Finder desktop through the generated handoff. `crabbox screenshot` also captured the same desktop at 1024x768. Release removed the VM; only the cached OCI base image remained.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `go vet ./...`\n- `go test -race ./...`\n- `scripts/test-go-modules.sh`\n- `scripts/check-go-coverage.sh 90.0` (`91.0%`)\n- Worker format, lint, typecheck, 349 tests, and Wrangler dry-run build\n- Script suite: 57 tests\n- Docs command/link/site generation checks\n- GoReleaser snapshot for configured targets, without publishing\n- Focused Tart provider race tests and architecture validation tests\n- Codex autoreview clean after all fixes; one startup-diagnostic regression was found, fixed, regression-tested, and re-reviewed clean\n\n## Exposure and compatibility notes\n\n- `CRABBOX_TART_PASSWORD` or mode-0600 user config controls the guest account password. There is intentionally no password CLI flag.\n- Multi-target providers such as Parallels keep their existing WebVNC routing.\n- `webvnc status`, `reset`, and `daemon` remain the Linux guest-daemon model and are not used for Tart.\n",
        "branch": "feat/tart-desktop-vnc",
